TIME_DETAIL.name: Time period details

descriptions.en:
When TIME_PERIOD refers to a date range, this attribute is used to provide metadata on the actual range the observation refers to (e.g. for period '2001-2003' TIME_PERIOD would be 2002 but the actual dates --2001-2003-- would be expressed
            here).

When TIME_PERIOD refers to a date range, this attribute is used to provide metadata on the actual range the observation refers to (e.g. for period '2001-2003' TIME_PERIOD would be 2002 but the actual dates --2001-2003-- would be expressed
